        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(sessions): rewrite first assistant flush",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n- Fixes the first-assistant flush path so a resumed no-assistant transcript is rewritten to the current in-memory buffer instead of appending that whole buffer onto existing disk contents.\r\n- This prevents duplicate session headers and duplicate pending user turns when resuming `header + user-only` transcripts.\r\n- Adds focused filesystem-backed coverage for the resume path.\r\n\r\n## Linked context\r\nCloses #89206.\r\n\r\n## Real behavior proof (required for external PRs)\r\n- Behavior or issue addressed: resumed session persistence duplicated existing transcript entries when the first assistant message caused the unflushed buffer to be written.\r\n- Real environment tested: disposable temp JSONL session file through `SessionManager.open(...)` and `appendMessage(...)`.\r\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch: `PNPM_CONFIG_OFFLINE=true corepack pnpm test src/agents/sessions/session-manager.test.ts -- --reporter=dot`.\r\n- Evidence after fix: the regression passes and asserts the on-disk transcript has exactly `session`, `message`, `message`, with one preserved user message.\r\n- Observed result after fix: first assistant flush rewrites the session file once instead of appending the full buffer over existing entries.\r\n- What was not tested: no live production resume was run against a real user transcript.\r\n- Proof limitations or environment constraints: I used a disposable temp transcript so private/local session data is not touched.\r\n\r\n## Tests and validation\r\n- `corepack pnpm exec oxfmt --write --threads=1 src/agents/sessions/session-manager.ts src/agents/sessions/session-manager.test.ts`\r\n- `PNPM_CONFIG_OFFLINE=true corepack pnpm test src/agents/sessions/session-manager.test.ts -- --reporter=dot` passed 1 Vitest file / 1 test.\r\n- `git diff --check -- src/agents/sessions/session-manager.ts src/agents/sessions/session-manager.test.ts`\r\n\r\n## Risk checklist\r\n- Did user-visible behavior change? Yes, resumed transcripts should no longer gain duplicate entries on first assistant flush.\r\n- Did config, environment, or migration behavior change? No.\r\n- Did security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change? No.\r\n- Highest-risk area: session persistence semantics. Mitigated by keeping the change to the existing unflushed first-assistant branch and covering the reported resume shape with a real temp file.\r\n\r\n## Current review state\r\nReady for maintainer review. No bot/reviewer comments have been addressed yet.",
